    "recap_headline": "University of Alabama at Birmingham Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BIRMINGHAM\n\u2013 UAB Baseball (11-7) hit five more home runs on Friday evening as the Blazers put together a 13-3 rout of Belmont (7-11). The Green and Gold now have 39 home runs this season which adds to their American Conference lead.\nUAB hit two home runs in a 5-run first inning.\nJohn Paul Head\ncontinued his home run hot streak as he blasted another opposite field home run for a 2-run shot.\nKevin Hall Jr.\nreturned from his brief hiatus and hit a 3-run home run to give the Blazers a 5-0 lead after one inning.\nBelmont got a single tally back in the top of the second. The Bruins cashed in a leadoff triple by Cavan McMeans and he scored on a Mike Sprockett RBI groundout.\nFour more Blazers crossed home in the bottom of the second by way of three more home runs.\nBaylor Roberts\nsmashed the second pitch he saw for a solo home run. Two batters later,\nJohn Paul Head\nhit his second home run in as many innings. The next hitter,\nLandon Beaver\nhit a towering shot just inside the right field foul pole to put UAB up 9-1 after two innings of play.\nNeither side would score again until Belmont's half of the fifth inning. The Bruins plated two on back to back base hits by Charlie Davis and Landon Godsey to cut the UAB lead to 9-3.\nThe Green and Gold put the game away in the bottom of the fifth by way of four unearned runs.\nAlex Dupuy\ndrove in\nWesley Helms\n,\nJohn Paul Head\nbrought home\nKevin Hall Jr.\nand Dupuy, and\nLandon Beaver\nsingled home Head to put UAB up, 13-3.\nNot to be outdone by his offense,\nMason Steele\ndelivered a stellar performance on the mound. The junior right-hander tossed all seven innings for his season-best in innings pitched and recorded his second straight win. Steele's final line was 7.0 innings pitched, eight strikeouts, three runs allowed, and surrendered only one walk.\nNOTES\n-\nMason Steele\nrecorded his second win in as many starts. Steele's strike percentage was at 65%.\n-\nJohn Paul Head\ntallied his fourth multi-home run game of the season. Head has now hit 12 home runs this season which leads the American Conference.\n- Head (6),\nAlex Dupuy\n(8),\nAndrew Hunt\n(6), and\nLandon Beaver\n(4) all recorded multi-hit games. Head leads the team with five 3-hit games.\n- Head also tied his career-high with six RBI.\n- Friday marked the sixth time this season the Blazers have hit at least four home runs in a game. UAB is 6-0 in those games.\n- The Blazers are 11-0 this season when scoring at least eight runs.\nUAB and Belmont square off for game two of the series on Saturday. First pitch from Young Memorial Field is slated for 2 p.m. on ESPN+.\nFOLLOW THE BLAZERS\nFor more information on the UAB Baseball team, follow @UAB_Baseball on X and Instagram.\nCompetitive Excellence Fund\nIn the current landscape of college athletics, the Competitive Excellence Fund has become integral in our department's mission to Win Champions, Graduate with Honors, and Impact the community. Through your generosity, our coaches will have the greatest opportunity to recruit, retain, and resource talented student athletes worthy of wearing a UAB uniform.\nClick here\nor connect with Blazer Boosters on how you can continue to fuel success."
